                <h1>Understanding ELISA: A Comprehensive Guide</h1>
                <p>ELISA, or Enzyme-Linked Immunosorbent Assay, is a widely used analytical technique for detecting and quantifying proteins, antibodies, and hormones. Developed in the 1970s, it has been instrumental in research, diagnostics, and vaccine development. ELISA is favored for its specificity, sensitivity, and versatility across various applications.</p>
